INSERT INTO `sdmatts_page_11` VALUES (2,'Why Us ?','<p>\r\n	dfdfd</p>\r\n','<h1>\n	WHAT MAKES US UNIQUE</h1>\n<br />\n<h2>\n	Huge Selection</h2>\n<p>\n	With over 150 Living Rooms, 115 Dining Rooms, and 100 Bedrooms, we have a huge selection of the best brands to meet any design style.</p>\n<h2>\n	Every Day Low Prices</h2>\n<p>\n	We&#39;re committed to offering the lowest possible prices on furniture. Our 10% Price Guarantee backs that up.</p>\n<h2>\n	One Low, Flat Delivery Fee</h2>\n<p>\n	Delivery and assembly of unlimited items for one low, flat delivery fee. Same day delivery available in certain areas for funiture purchases made before 4:00p.m.</p>\n<h2>\n	Fun Room</h2>\n<p>\n	We have a supervised kid&#39;s fun room where children over 42 inches tall can watch movies and play video games while their parents shop unencumbered.</p>\n<h2>\n	Shoppertainment</h2>\n<p>\n	Enjoy our theater-sized big screens from our sea of recliners with some complementary Starbucks coffee..</p>\n<h2>\n	Accessories</h2>\n<p>\n	We have accessories to spice up every room in your home: lamps, plants, artwork, mirrors and many more. Stop by one of our store locations to view our full line of accessories today.</p>\n<h2>\n	Gift Cards</h2>\n<p>\n	With fully customizable amounts, gift cards are a great gift idea for that someone in need of some new home furnishings. Only available in store, please see a cashier for details.</p>\n','fdf','dfd','Active','information','2006-10-14'),(3,'Privacy Policy','<p>\r\n	fsdf</p>\r\n','<h2>\r\n	&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<h4>\r\n	<span style=\"color:#daa520;\"><span style=\"font-size: 36px;\">Privacy Policy</span></span></h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>\r\n	What is Personal Information?</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Personal information is information that specifically identifies an individual such as a customer&rsquo;s name, address, telephone number, e&ndash;mail address, credit card or other account number, and information about that individual&rsquo;s activities when directly linked to that person, such as information about his or her purchases. Personal information also includes demographic information such as date of birth, gender, geographic area and preferences when such information is linked to other personal information that identifies you.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Personal information does not include &ldquo;aggregate&rdquo; information. Aggregate information is data we collect about a group or category of products, services or customers, from which individual customer identities have been removed. In other words, information about how you use a service may be collected and combined with information about how others use the same service, but no personal information will be included in the resulting data. Likewise, information about the products you purchase may be collected and combined with information about the products purchased by others. Aggregate data helps us understand trends and customer needs so that we can better consider new products and services, and tailor existing products and services to customer desires.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2>\r\n	Personal Information We Collect</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	You provide personal information to us in a number of ways when you visit our Site. For example, you provide us with personal information when you: (1) purchase products and services, (2) create an user account, (3) sign up for our email list or electronic newsletters, (3) participate in surveys, sweepstakes, and promotions, (4) create a wish list, (5) elect to share content from this website with your friends,(6) register on our site and create an account using already established social networking accounts such as Facebook and Twitter, (7) submit a warranty registration, and (8) contact us by email for any reason (such as to request customer service or provide us with your comments/feedback). We collect your name, billing and shipping addresses, email address, friend&#39;s email address, phone number, fax number, credit card information, login information, order information, wish list, and payment settings in this manner. We also collect personal information from you if you submit an online job application or resume to us, including your name and email address, as well as other employment related information that you provide to us at your option.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	When you visit our Site, some information is also automatically collected, such as your computer&rsquo;s Internet Protocol (IP) address, your computer&rsquo;s operating system, the browser type, the address of a referring web site, and the time and date of your visit and purchases. This information is collected through the use of &ldquo;cookies.&rdquo; Cookies are small files that are stored on your computer by a web site to give you a unique identification. We use cookies on our Site to help optimize your shopping experience by storing information about your preferences, allowing us to customize our site according to your individual interests, to speed up your searches, and to recognize you when you return to our site. For example, we use cookies to keep track of your shopping cart and to store your shipping information for delivery of future orders. We treat this information as personal information if we combine it with or link it to any of the personally identifying information mentioned above. Otherwise, it is used in the aggregate only.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	You may refuse to accept cookies by activating the setting on your browser which allows you to refuse the setting of cookies. However, if you select this setting you may be unable to access certain parts of our site.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We also use &quot;pixel tags&quot; on our site (also known as &quot;Internet tags&quot;, &quot;web beacons&quot;, or &quot;clear GIFS&quot;), which are tiny graphic images. Pixel tags help us analyze our customers&#39; online behavior and measure the effectiveness of our website and our advertising. We work with service providers that help us track, collect, and analyze this information.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2>\r\n	How We Use Personal Information</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	In general, we use personal information to process your requests or transactions and provide you with high-quality products and services or to inform you about other products or services we think will be of interest. For example, we use your information to deliver products or provide services you have purchased. When we use personal information in our internal marketing efforts, we provide you with choices (See Choice below) and do not disclose the information to third parties except as described in this privacy policy. We may also receive information from third parties with whom we have business relationships, and will combine this information with the other personal information we maintain about you. In such cases, this privacy policy governs this information.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Pixel tags on our site may be used to collect information about your visit, included the pages you view, the features you use, the links you click, and other actions you take in connection with the site. This information may include your computer&#39;s IP address, your browser type, your operating system, date and time information, and other technical information about your computer. We may also track certain information about the identity of the website you visited immediately before coming to our site.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Pixel tags and cookies in our emails to you may be used to track your interactions with those messages, such as when you receive, open, or click a link in an email message from us.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We also work with business partners that use tracking technologies to deliver advertisements on our behalf across the Internet. These companies may collect information about your visits to our site and your inter action with our advertising and other communications.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We may combine the information we collect through cookies and pixel tags with other information we have collected from you. This information may be used to improve our website, to personalize your online experience, to help us deliver information to you, to determine the effectiveness of our advertising, and for other internal business purposes.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2>\r\n	Sharing of Personal Information</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	We do not sell, rent or share personal information with third parties without your prior consent except in the limited circumstances described in this privacy policy. We share personal information with third-party vendors who assist us in performing internal functions necessary to operate our business. These functions may include, for example, distributing emails, managing a database of customer information, providing fraud prevention, analyzing data, providing marketing assistance, processing credit card payments and fulfilling/delivering orders. We require our third party vendors to keep such information confidential and to only use the information for the purpose it was provided. We are not responsible for any additional information you provide directly to these parties, and we encourage you to become familiar with their practices before disclosing information directly to them.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In addition, information about our customers, including personally identifiable information, may be disclosed as part of any merger, acquisition, debt financing, sale of company assets, as well as in the event of an insolvency, bankruptcy or receivership in which personally identifiable information could be transferred to third parties as one of the business assets of the company.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	We also disclose personal information when we believe it is appropriate to comply with the law (e.g., a lawful subpoena, warrant or court order); to enforce or apply this privacy policy or our other policies or agreements; to initiate, render, bill, and collect for amounts owed to us; to protect our or our customers&acute; rights, property or safety; to protect our customers from fraudulent, abusive, or unlawful use of our Site; or if we reasonably believe that an emergency involving immediate danger of death or serious physical injury to any person requires disclosure of communications or justifies disclosure of records without delay.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	In addition, information about our customers, including personally identifiable information, may be disclosed as part of any merger, acquisition, debt financing, sale of company assets, as well as in the event of an insolvency, bankruptcy or receivership in which personally identifiable information could be transferred to third parties as one of the business assets of the company.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2>\r\n	Links to Other Web Sites</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	Our Site contains links to other web sites. Any personal information you provide on the linked pages is provided directly to that third party and is subject to that third party&#39;s privacy policy. Except as described above, we are not responsible for the content or privacy and security practices and policies of web sites to which we link. Links from our web site to third parties or to other sites are provided for your convenience. We encourage you to learn about their privacy and security practices and policies before providing them with personal information.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2>\r\n	Use of our Site by Children</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	We encourage parents to take an active interest in their children&rsquo;s use of the Internet. Our site is not meant for children and we do not intend to collect information from children who are under 16 years of age. If you are under 16, you should not provide information on our Site and should ask your parent to do so for you.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2>\r\n	Security</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	We have put into place reasonable security measures in an effort to protect personal information while it is under our control. All personal information relating to our customers is stored in a secure environment separate from our Site.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2>\r\n	Choice</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	We give you the following options to opt-out of receiving communications from us or to request that we correct or delete your personal information: (1) contact our customer service department by phone at 700-200-405 (2) email us at <a href=\"mailto:customerservice@sleeptrain.com\">customerservice@sleeptrain.com</a>; or (3) write to us at the following address with your request:</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://localhost/mattress_yii_old\">619.210.3714</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://localhost/mattress_yii_old\">707 L St. #C108</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://localhost/mattress_yii_old\">Chula Vista, Ca. 91911</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<a href=\"http://localhost/mattress_yii_old\">*L Stret Storage</a></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	If, in the future, we decide to share personal information with any third parties for their own marketing purposes, we will update this privacy policy to reflect such change and provide you with the opportunity to opt-out of such disclosure of your personal information.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2>\r\n	Policy Changes</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	We will periodically modify our Privacy Policy so that it remains relevant and current with changing technologies, applicable laws, evolving business practices, and the needs of our customers. Whenever we modify our privacy policy, we will post the revised policy here, with an updated revision date. If we make material changes to the policy or in how we will use your personal information, we will also notify you by other means, such as sending an email and/or posting a notice on our corporate website and/or social media pages prior to the changes taking effect. We will also keep prior versions of this Privacy Policy in an archive for your review. We encourage you to periodically review the privacy statements for the products and services you use to learn how we are protecting your information. If you continue to use our website after notice of the change has been given, you will be deemed to have accepted such changes.</p>\r\n<hr />\r\n<h2>\r\n	Your Comments or Concerns</h2>\r\n<p>\r\n	We welcome your feedback. If you have any comments or concerns about this privacy policy or would like to contact us for any reason, you may reach a customer service representative via e-mail at <a class=\"ApplyClass\" href=\"mailto:customerservice@sleeptrain.com\">mattress@gmail.com</a> or phone at 98546745625.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	You may unsubscribe from our emails by clicking on the Unsubscribe hyperlink at the bottom of the email. We will note in our database that you have elected to opt out of future emails from our company. Your record will still remain in our database but you will not receive any future mailings unless we manually opt you back in. You may also choose to opt out of emails by sending an email to us at <a class=\"ApplyClass\" href=\"mailto:customerservice@sleeptrain.com\">mattress@gmail.com</a>. If you choose to opt out with this method, please be sure to include the email address that you would like us to unsubscribe.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	This web-site tracks users to personalize and optimize your browsing experience. You may opt out of this tracking by clicking the link below. This will set a cookie in your browser that will turn off this tracking. Please note that if you delete your cookies, use a different browser, or buy a new computer, you will have to opt out again.</p>\r\n','fdf','dfd','Active','ffd','2014-10-06'),(4,'Delivery','<p>\r\n	ds</p>\r\n','<h1>\n	<span style=\"color:#faba5b;\">Delivery</span></h1>\n<h2>\n	Free Same Day Delivery</h2>\n<p>\n	<img align=\"right\" alt=\"Mattress in a home\" height=\"275\" hspace=\"10\" src=\"http://demandware.edgesuite.net/aaor_prd/on/demandware.static/Sites-SleepTrain-Site/Sites-SleepTrain-Library/default/v1412369656715/images/education/delivery-bedroom.jpg\" vspace=\"10\" width=\"350\" />Within any of our local delivery zones, purchase any in-stock item by 2 pm, and our professional red carpet delivery team will deliver your mattress for free the same day. Our delivery team will remove your old mattress, set up your new one and even wear cloth booties to ensure that your home stays clean &mdash; all at no cost to you! Delivery service is available 7 days a week.</p>\n<p>\n	<em>Soft goods may be shipped via UPS if they are not purchased with a mattress. Same day delivery is not available in some outlying areas. Please call (800) 378-2337 or chat with us if you have any questions.</em></p>\n<h2>\n	Free Delivery (Out-of-Market)</h2>\n<p>\n	With Sleep Train, you can enjoy free delivery of your purchase anywhere in the continental U.S. Our delivery team will deliver and set up your new mattress within 1-4 weeks of the earliest date you are available to receive your product. You will be contacted within 3 weeks of your order to schedule a delivery time.</p>\n<p>\n	All deliveries include set up in the room of your choice (including up to 2 flights of stairs), removal of packaging and the removal of one mattress set. Further accommodations can be requested at the time of delivery for additional fees. If you miss your agreed upon delivery time, you will be charged a $99 re-delivery fee.</p>\n<h2>\n	Free Shipping</h2>\n<p>\n	Small items such as sheets and pillows may be shipped to you separately by an external shipping carrier.</p>\n<h3>\n	Preparing your home for delivery</h3>\n<p>\n	With just a few minor preparations, your home will be ready for delivery of your new mattress set:</p>\n<ul>\n	<li>\n		Clear a delivery path from your front door to your bedroom &mdash; removing obstructions such as furniture, breakables and valuables.</li>\n	<li>\n		If the delivery path includes narrow hallways or stairs that may introduce the potential for damage to your home or new mattress, the delivery team may ask you to sign a damage waiver in order to proceed with delivery.</li>\n	<li>\n		Contain any house pets in a safe place during the delivery and set up of your new mattress set.</li>\n	<li>\n		We require that the person receiving and signing the delivery acknowledgment must be at least 18 years of age.</li>\n	<li>\n		Sleep Train must verify the identity of all C.O.D. customers. We require that all C.O.D. customers be present, with valid I.D. at the time of delivery. Local delivery areas only.</li>\n	<li>\n		Due to the limited allocation of space on our delivery trucks, we are unable to remove more items than are delivered.</li>\n</ul>\n','ds','xcx','Active','information','2014-10-06'),(5,'Warranty','<p>\r\n	fdf</p>\r\n','<h1>\n	<span style=\"color:#faba5b;\">Mattress Warranty</span></h1>\n<p>\n	Sometimes even the best quality products will show early signs of wear, tear or manufacturer defect. During and beyond your 100-night comfort exchange period, the majority of products we sell are covered by national manufacturer&#39;s warranties. Below are several videos to review when considering a warranty claim.</p>\n','fgf','gfg','Active','information','2006-10-14'),(6,'satisfection','<p>\r\n	sdsdsd</p>\r\n','<h4>\r\n	Satisfection Assurance</h4>\r\n<p>\r\n	&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Getting a good night&rsquo;s sleep on a mattress often comes down to one key factor: design of the coil. Sherwood mattresses feature an innovative open coil design that provides up to 21% more support than conventional mattresses.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Why is the coil so important? The coil in a mattress supports your body, surrounding it with comfort.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	The core of any mattress is its support system, and most mass-market mattresses feature variants of an 80-year-old, Great Depression-era design. These spring units don&rsquo;t offer the consistent, edge-to-edge support for your body.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	Many sleepers move upwards to 35 times in a single night. And, if you share a bed, that&rsquo;s close to 70 adjustments. On a traditional innerspring</p>\r\n<p>\r\n	<h4>Satisfection Assurance</h4></p>\r\n<p>\r\n	mattress, you&rsquo;ll likely feel those disturbances. Sherwood mattresses feature a luxurious pocketed spring coil system. This allows each spring to respond independently to the shape of your body and improve conformance while virtually eliminating sleep-disturbing motion transfer. Our coil system creates a world of good for your back and spine, in and out of bed. It provides years of comfortable sleep.</p>\r\n','hg','hgh','Active','information','2014-10-31'),(7,'Contact','<p>Arrange a SLEEP  Test</p>','<p>Comfort Touch Mattress &amp; Electropedic Adjustable Beds offers relaxing, high quality adjustable beds and specialty mattresses in San Diego, Ca.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>At Comfort Touch Mattress and Adjustable Beds, we have been serving the San Diego area for over 40 years. We strive to assist our customers in finding the perfect mattress for their individual needs. We offer the largest collection of adjustable beds as well as standard beds from all national manufacturers on display in our store. This helps you in comparing each brand, side-by-side, to find the one that best suits your body type, health needs and comfort requirements. Some of top brands includes Electropedic Adjustable Beds, Spinal Care, Latex International and more.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We have been an A+ Rated company since 1977 with the San Diego Better Business Bureau, and we&#39;re recognized as one of the top 100 businesses in San Diego.</p>\r\n','hello','hello','Active','information','2007-11-14');
